A unique collection of pictures taken during the early days of photography have given a rare insight into Victorian Britain.

The 350 images were taken by amateur photographer Emma Johnston, who is considered to be one of the 19th century's lost figures of the art form.

Experts say very little is known about the middle class woman apart from the fact she lived in Hampstead.

