Many of her photogrpahs show the long list of visitors she welcomed to the Manor House, where she lived with her unmarried father.

The first photographic images were taken in Britain in 1834 with the common process for developing pictures beginning in 1841.

Miss Johnston's pictures are believed to have been taken between 1858 and 1864.

